<p class="lead mb-5">
	We realize how important it is to maintain dental health because how it closely relates to the nervous system in our brain. Current dental care had developed to become better. Not only there is a method to relieve pain, prevention and reconstruction method are also started to be developed. <span class="text-secondary font-weight-semibold">Confi-dent</span> as dental care center provides several services, as follow :
</p>

<h4 class="mb-2 text-primary"><i class="fas fa-check mr-2"></i>Dental check up</h4>
<p class="mb-4">Dentists recommended a dental check-up at least twice a year and this will allow for a detailed examination of your teeth, gums and mouth. This will prevent painful and expensive dental treatments.</p>

<h4 class="mb-2 text-primary"><i class="fas fa-check mr-2"></i>Teeth whitening</h4>
<p class="mb-4">Teeth Whitening has become very popular treatment tourist in Bali over the past years due to the excellent results provided and being a very affordable dental treatment.</p>

<h4 class="mb-2 text-primary"><i class="fas fa-check mr-2"></i>Dental filling</h4>
<p class="mb-4">When a tooth has a cavity or undergone trauma a dental filling is required to provide strength and protect the root and pulp inside the tooth from further damage and restore the natural shape.</p>

<h4 class="mb-2 text-primary"><i class="fas fa-check mr-2"></i>Extraction</h4>
<p class="mb-4">If your tooth has been chipped, broken or damaged from excessive decay your dentists will first attempt to save the tooth. However, in some situations it’s not possible and the tooth requires an extraction.</p>

<h4 class="mb-2 text-primary"><i class="fas fa-check mr-2"></i>Periodontal disease</h4>
<p class="mb-4">Over 95% of our patients have had gum disease at some point in their life and often this starts as swollen and bleeding gums caused by bacteria and if left untreated it can cause damage to the gums and teeth.</p>

<h4 class="mb-2 text-primary"><i class="fas fa-check mr-2"></i>Teeth grinding</h4>
<p class="mb-4">Many of our patients do not realize that they grind their teeth until it’s too late and they have damaged and fractured their teeth. Our dental clinic provides a number of solutions to teeth grinding.</p>

<h4 class="mb-2 text-primary"><i class="fas fa-check mr-2"></i>Dental veneers</h4>
<p class="mb-4">Dental veneers are a thin shell that is placed over your tooth. It is mostly used to restore chipped or worn teeth and strengthens your natural teeth, which can provide a perfect white smile.</p>

<h4 class="mb-2 text-primary"><i class="fas fa-check mr-2"></i>Denture</h4>
<p class="mb-4">A denture is a set of removable false teeth often required if you have had your natural teeth damaged or if your teeth have been extracted. Typically made from acrylic they will match your normal teeth.</p>

<h4 class="mb-2 text-primary"><i class="fas fa-check mr-2"></i>Dental crown</h4>
<p class="mb-4">A dental crown is a dental cap typically made from ceramic and appears like a natural tooth. A dental crown is used when your tooth has been damaged, cracked or discoloured.</p>

<h4 class="mb-2 text-primary"><i class="fas fa-check mr-2"></i>Root canal therapy</h4>
<p class="mb-4">If the internal pulp of the tooth has become infected or the tooth root has been damaged a root canal if often required. However, please don’t worry root canals are painless and will save your tooth.</p>

<h4 class="mb-2 text-primary"><i class="fas fa-check mr-2"></i>Dental implant</h4>
<p class="mb-4">If your tooth has been damaged dental implants provide an excellent solution. A dental implant is a titanium screw, which is placed into the jawbone, and a dental crown is attached.</p>
